  "title": "Administrative Assistant",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Prepare quotations, proposals, and related materials to support client discussions.</li>\n  <li>Organize and assemble documents required for client review and signing.</li>\n  <li>Manage the submission of completed forms and paperwork to the appropriate teams or service providers.</li>\n  <li>Follow up on ongoing matters such as pending documents, incomplete requirements, or payment issues.</li>\n  <li>Maintain and update client information, assist with service requests, and coordinate with external partners when needed.</li>\n  <li>Oversee general administrative tasks, including filing, correspondence, and ensuring documents meet internal guidelines.</li>\n  <li>Support the team with scheduling, meeting arrangements, and preparation of basic reports.</li>\n  <li>Carry out routine secretarial and administrative duties, along with any additional tasks assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Business Administration, Finance, or related field</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Interested applicants please send your resume in MS Word format and attention it to Rachel Yeo (R22104385).</p>\n<p>Shortlisted candidates will be notified</p>\n<p>Data provided is for recruitment purposes only</p>\n<p>www.ambition.com.sg</p>\n<p>EA Registration Number: R22104385</p>\n<p>Business Registration Number: 200611680D. Licence Number: 10C5117</p>",
